## Ignore Visual Studio temporary files, build results, and
## files generated by popular Visual Studio add-ons.
##
## This .gitignore file is a combination of:
## 1. The Visual Studio .gitignore from GitHub (https://github.com/github/gitignore)
## 2. Common .NET exclusions

# Build results
[Dd]ebug/
[Dd]ebugPublic/
[Rr]elease/
[Rr]eleases/
x64/
x86/
[Ww][In][32]/
[Aa][Rr][Mm]/
[Aa][Rr][Mm]64/
bld/
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
**/bin/
**/obj/
log/
logs/

# Visual Studio 2015/2017/2019/2022 cache and settings
.vs/
# Uncomment if you use Visual Studio Code
.vscode/

# User-specific files
*.rsuser
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# User-specific files (MonoDevelop/Xamarin Studio)
*.userprefs

# Mono auto generated files
mono_crash.*

# [Bb]uild results
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*

# Azure Cloud Service project settings
*.azurePubxml
*.azureServicePackages

# Others
.env
ClientBin/
~$*
*~
*.dbmdl
*.dbproj.schemaview
*.jfm
*.pfx
*.publishsettings
orleans.dot

# .NET Core
project.lock.json
project.fragment.lock.json
artifacts/

# ASP.NET Core
appsettings.Development.json
# Uncomment the line below if you want to ignore appsettings.json
# appsettings.json

# Rider
.idea/
*.sln.iml

# User secrets (if used)
secrets.json

# Node.js (if you add a frontend later)
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
